<div class="row">
	<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
		<h2>Create a pie chart</h2>
		<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4">
			<p>Upload a file containing 2 tab-separated columns, where the first column lists the categories and the second column lists the absolute value for each category.</p>
			<p>To configure the chart title and unit of measurement, you may add their values to the top of your file like this:</p>
			<code>#title=My amazing pie chart</code><br/>
			<code>#unit=kittens</code><br/>
			<code>category1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;100</code><br/>
			<code>category2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;500</code><br/>
			<code>...</code>
			<%= simple_form_for :pie, url: "/charts/display_pie", :html => { :multipart => true }, :remote => true do |form| %>
			  <br/>Select base color: <%= form.text_field :color, :value => '#317777' %><br/>
			  Select data file: <%= form.file_field :data %><br/>
			  <%= form.submit 'Bake the pie', :class => 'btn btn-primary' %>
			<% end  %>
		</div>
		<div id="pie" class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-8 chart-display"></div>
	</div>
</div>
